 as Acting Commander, as Deputy Controller, DC, B.U. Yahaya, who was in charge of enforcement of Federal Operations Unit, Zone A, will Act as Customs Area Controller, CAC, of the unit. The other two new postings are DC, C.D. Wada who now takes over as Acting CAC of Seme Command and Assistant Controller, AC, A.G. Kakudi is now Acting Officer in Charge of the Strike Force Zone A. The circular read in part, “These appointments take immediate effect. The Affected officers are therefore to handover and takeover immediately.” The Comptroller-General of Customs, (CGC) Col. Hamid Ali, (rtd) has directed the immediate removal of all illegal Customs check-points, across the country. July 25, 2017 In "News" OF all the chief executives of the Nigerian Customs Service to date, none has been more powerful than Colonel Hameed Ibrahim Alli (retd.), the sixty-four year old post graduate criminologist, from Dass Local Government Area of Bauchi State. November 26, 2019 In "News" The Comptroller-General of Customs, Col. Hamid Ali (retd), has directed the immediate removal of all illegal Customs check-points across the country. July 26, 2017 In "News"